## Commands

- `npm test`
- `cargo test --manifest-path src-tauri/Cargo.toml`
- Add lint and typecheck commands to the default verification path when they are introduced

## Code Style

- Rust: keep parsing, SQLite access, and filesystem coordination in the Tauri backend
- TypeScript/React: keep canonical content in SQLite rather than client persistence
- Zustand: use small domain-focused stores for UI/session state only
- Styling: prefer styled wrappers and layout composition over deep Semantic UI React overrides

## Atomic Design Rules

- Use Atomic Design for shared React UI components in `src/components`
- Keep feature-specific business logic, route composition, and data-connected flows in `src/features` and `src/routes`
- Build from simple to complex: atoms -> molecules -> organisms -> templates -> pages
- Atoms should be stateless or contain UI-only state such as focus or hover
- Molecules may combine multiple atoms for one focused purpose, but should not fetch data or connect to global state
- Organisms may compose molecules and atoms, and can contain feature-level UI logic or connect to stores when needed
- Templates define page structure and layout only; they should not contain real content or data loading
- Pages should live in `src/routes` or feature entry screens, use templates where appropriate, and connect to real data and navigation

## Component Placement

- Put reusable primitives such as buttons, inputs, labels, icons, badges, and loaders in `src/components/atoms`
- Put focused composite controls such as search bars, form fields, filter rows, and card previews in `src/components/molecules`
- Put larger reusable sections such as dictionary search panels, card editors, collection sidebars, and review panels in `src/components/organisms`
- Put layout shells such as main app layout, split-pane layout, and modal page layouts in `src/components/templates`
- If a component is tightly coupled to one domain and unlikely to be reused across features, keep it inside that feature instead of forcing it into the shared atomic tree

## Naming And Imports

- Use PascalCase directory and component names for atomic components
- Template components should end with `Layout`
- Route-level page components should end with `Page`
- Prefer barrel exports for each atomic level and from `src/components/index.ts`
- Use path aliases for cross-level imports, for example `@/components/atoms` or `@/components/organisms`
- Avoid skipping levels in composition unless the simpler abstraction adds no value

## UI Verification

- New atoms, molecules, and organisms should be easy to test in isolation
- Shared interactive atoms should support refs and accessible states when appropriate
- Prefer isolated component stories or equivalent visual fixtures for atoms, molecules, and organisms when the project adds a component preview workflow

